---Instructions to build required freehep C++ library (Linux):

Need freehep version from Oct 31 20000 (later versions use HepRep2, not HepRep1).

Some of the following is taken from the freehep checkout
instructions available at:
http://java.freehep.org/source.thtml

Checkout freehep as follows:
setenv CVSROOT :pserver:anoncvs@cvs.freehep.org:/nfs/slac/g/jas/fhroot
cvs login
CVS Password: jascvs
cvs co -D 20001031 freehep

Make sure you have a copy of the Java Development Kit
(called JDK or SDK), not just the Java Runtime Environment (JRE).
The latter doesn't contain the compiler, necessary for the make.
The Java Development Kit is freely available from
http://java.sun.com/j2se/

Make the freehep C++ library as follows:
  setenv JDK_HOME your_java_directory
  setenv FREEHEP your_freehep_directory
  setenv OS Linux
  cd $FREEHEP
  tools/bootstrap-freehep
  tools/ant clean
  tools/ant
  gmake clean
  gmake
The gmake will end with some errors, but they can be ignored.


---Instructions to build Geant4 (Linux):

Check out geant4 and CLHEP1.7.

  setenv SCRATCH your_scratch_directory
  setenv JDK_HOME your_java_directory
  setenv FREEHEP your_freehep_directory
  setenv G4INSTALL your_geant4_directory
  setenv CLHEP_BASE_DIR your_CLHEP1.7_directory

  setenv G4SYSTEM Linux-g++
  setenv G4BIN $SCRATCH/bin
  setenv G4LIB $SCRATCH/lib
  setenv G4TMP $SCRATCH/tmp
  setenv G4DEBUG 1
  setenv G4LEVELGAMMADATA $G4INSTALL/data/PhotonEvaporation
  setenv LD_LIBRARY_PATH "/usr/local/lib:$CLHEP_BASE_DIR/lib:$FREEHEP/lib/$G4SYSTEM:$JDK_HOME/jre/lib/i386/hotspot:$JDK_HOME/jre/lib/i386"
  setenv CLASSPATH "$FREEHEP/lib/freehep-2d.jar:$FREEHEP/lib/freehep-heprep.jar:$FREEHEP/lib/freehep-base.jar:$FREEHEP/lib/xerces.jar:$FREEHEP/lib/collections.jar"
  setenv G4VIS_BUILD_HEPREP_DRIVER 1
  setenv G4VIS_USE_HEPREP 1
  setenv G4_HEPREP_OSNAME linux
  setenv G4_HEPREP_ARCH i386

  cd $G4INSTALL/source
  gmake > & gmake.log &

  cd $G4INSTALL/source/visualization/test
  touch test19.cc
  gmake


---Instructions to run Geant4 to make heprep xml:

remove test19.g4m to make the example wait for interactive input.

   ln -s $G4BIN/Linux-g++/test19 .
   test19
   /vis/open HepRep
   /vis/drawVolume
   /vis/viewer/update

creates output file:
~/wiredwork/G4/geant4/source/visualization/test/HepRepTest.xml


Joseph Perl
